        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "RSS feeds generated with Zend_Feed::importBuilder(new Zend_Feed_Builder(...), 'rss')->saveXML() do not validate if one of the iTunes categories consists of a main and a sub element. The tag for the main element is closed before the sub element is enclosed as shown below.\r\n\r\nResult as generated by Zend_Feed:\r\n\r\n    <itunes:category xmlns:itunes=\"http:\/\/www.itunes.com\/DTDs\/Podcast-1.0.dtd\" text=\"Arts\"\/>\r\n    <itunes:category xmlns:itunes=\"http:\/\/www.itunes.com\/DTDs\/Podcast-1.0.dtd\" text=\"Arts\"\/>\r\n    <itunes:category xmlns:itunes=\"http:\/\/www.itunes.com\/DTDs\/Podcast-1.0.dtd\" text=\"Performing Arts\"\/>\r\n    <itunes:category xmlns:itunes=\"http:\/\/www.itunes.com\/DTDs\/Podcast-1.0.dtd\"\/>\r\n\r\n\r\nExpected:\r\n\r\n    <itunes:category xmlns:itunes=\"http:\/\/www.itunes.com\/DTDs\/Podcast-1.0.dtd\" text=\"Arts\"\/> <!-- Only main category is ok -->\r\n    <itunes:category xmlns:itunes=\"http:\/\/www.itunes.com\/DTDs\/Podcast-1.0.dtd\" text=\"Arts\">\r\n       <itunes:category xmlns:itunes=\"http:\/\/www.itunes.com\/DTDs\/Podcast-1.0.dtd\" text=\"Performing Arts\"\/>\r\n    <itunes:category xmlns:itunes=\"http:\/\/www.itunes.com\/DTDs\/Podcast-1.0.dtd\"\/>\r\n\r\nor from http:\/\/www.apple.com\/itunes\/podcasts\/specs.html: \r\n\r\n<itunes:category text=\"Technology\">\r\n<itunes:category text=\"Gadgets\"\/>\r\n<\/itunes:category>\r\n<itunes:category text=\"TV &amp; Film\"\/>"
